---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const githubUrl = 'https://github.com/maxistar/Voice-Inbox';
const releaseUrl = `${githubUrl}/releases`;
---
<Layout title="Legal" description="Voice Inbox legal, support, privacy, and publication information.">
  <style>
    .legal {
      max-width: 900px;
    }
    .table {
      display: grid;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      overflow: hidden;
      background: var(--surface);
    }
    .row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .row:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .row strong, .row span {
      padding: 14px 16px;
    }
    .row strong {
      background: var(--surface-strong);
    }
    @media (max-width: 680px) {
      .row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .row strong { padding-bottom: 4px; }
      .row span { padding-top: 4px; }
    }
  </style>

  <article class="legal">
    <p class="eyebrow">Legal information</p>
    <h1>App and publication details</h1>
    <p>
      This page collects information useful for users and app store publication preparation.
      Fields marked as placeholders must be reviewed and replaced by the maintainer before store submission.
    </p>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>App information</h2>
      <div class="table">
        <div class="row"><strong>App name</strong><span>Voice Inbox</span></div>
        <div class="row"><strong>Android package</strong><span><code>me.maxistar.voiceinbox</code></span></div>
        <div class="row"><strong>iOS bundle status</strong><span>iOS MVP in development; final bundle identifier and store listing details must be confirmed before release.</span></div>
        <div class="row"><strong>Developer / publisher</strong><span>TODO: maintainer legal or publisher name</span></div>
        <div class="row"><strong>Support contact</strong><span>TODO: support email or support URL</span></div>
        <div class="row"><strong>Privacy policy</strong><span><a href="../privacy/">Privacy page</a></span></div>
        <div class="row"><strong>Source code</strong><span><a href={githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">{githubUrl}</a></span></div>
        <div class="row"><strong>Downloads</strong><span><a href={releaseUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Releases</a></span></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Requirements and limitations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Requires an ARM64 Android device running Android 7.0 (API 24) or later.</li>
        <li>iOS support is currently an MVP and should not be described as full Android parity or a final App Store release.</li>
        <li>Requires network access for the first speech model download.</li>
        <li>Requires about 704 MiB of free storage for model installation.</li>
        <li>Scheduled transcription uses Android background work and is not an exact alarm.</li>
        <li>Speech recognition accuracy is not guaranteed and may vary by audio quality, accent, language, and recording conditions.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>License and acknowledgements</h2>
      <p>
        Voice Inbox is distributed from its public source repository. TODO: confirm final app license text
        and add third-party acknowledgements for AndroidX, Apple platform APIs, ONNX Runtime, Rust crates, Kotlin Multiplatform libraries, and the speech model before publication.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Important notice</h2>
      <p>
        This legal page is structured publication information, not legal advice. Review it before publishing to Google Play or another app store.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
